Package: transmux
Architecture: amd64
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, dotnet-runtime-10.0, ffmpeg
Description: Clean desktop audio/video converter powered by Lumyn
 Transmux is a minimal, clean desktop audio/video converter powered by
 FFmpeg. Drop in a media file, inspect its format and streams, pick an
 output format, and convert — all without touching a command line.
 .
 Features:
  - Open audio and video files via file picker or drag and drop
  - Inspect detected format, video stream, audio streams, and subtitle tracks
  - Convert to MP4, WebM, MKV, AVI, MOV, MP3, AAC, FLAC, OGG, WAV, or Opus
  - Include subtitles in output, extract to separate .srt/.ass, or strip them
  - Live progress bar with speed and ETA
  - Cancel in-flight conversions
  - Remember last output directory and format between sessions
 .
 Built with .NET 10 and Avalonia UI.
